                    <p>Our home galaxy spans approximately <span class="highlight">100,000-200,000 light-years</span> in diameter.</p>
                    <p>Contains <span class="highlight">200-400 billion stars</span> and has a mass of <span class="highlight">1.5 trillion solar masses</span>.</p>
                    <p>The galaxy is <span class="highlight">13.6 billion years old</span> and rotates once every <span class="highlight">225-250 million years</span>.</p>
                    <p>Our Sun orbits at a distance of <span class="highlight">26,000 light-years</span> from the galactic center.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="info-card">
                    <div class="icon">‚òÄÔ∏è</div>
                    <h3>The Sun</h3>
                    <p>Diameter: <span class="highlight">1,391,000 kilometers</span> (109 times Earth's diameter).</p>
                    <p>Distance from Earth: <span class="highlight">149.6 million kilometers</span> (1 Astronomical Unit).</p>
                    <p>Light takes <span class="highlight">8 minutes 20 seconds</span> to reach Earth.</p>
                    <p>Surface temperature: <span class="highlight">5,500¬∞C</span> and core temperature: <span class="highlight">15 million¬∞C</span>.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="info-card">
                    <div class="icon">ü™ê</div>
                    <h3>Jupiter</h3>
                    <p>Diameter: <span class="highlight">139,820 kilometers</span> (11 times Earth's diameter).</p>
                    <p>Can fit <span class="highlight">1,300 Earths</span> inside Jupiter.</p>
                    <p>Great Red Spot: A massive storm active for <span class="highlight">at least 350+ years</span>.</p>
                    <p>Distance from Sun: <span class="highlight">778 million kilometers</span>.</p>
                    <p>Has <span class="highlight">95 known moons</span>, including the 4 Galilean moons.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="info-card">
                    <div class="icon">üí´</div>
                    <h3>Saturn</h3>
                    <p>Diameter: <span class="highlight">116,460 kilometers</span> (9.5 times Earth).</p>
                    <p>Famous for its spectacular ring system extending <span class="highlight">282,000 kilometers</span> in diameter.</p>
                    <p>Has <span class="highlight">146 known moons</span>, the largest being Titan.</p>
                    <p>Average temperature: <span class="highlight">-140¬∞C</span> on cloud tops.</p>
                    <p>Takes <span class="highlight">29.5 Earth years</span> to orbit the Sun.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="info-card">
                    <div class="icon">üï≥Ô∏è</div>
                    <h3>Black Holes</h3>
                    <p>Formed from collapsed massive stars with density so extreme that nothing can escape their gravitational pull.</p>
                    <p>Event Horizon: The point of no return, beyond which <span class="highlight">not even light can escape</span>.</p>
                    <p>Sagittarius A*: Supermassive black hole at the center of Milky Way with mass of <span class="highlight">4.1 million solar masses</span>.</p>
                    <p>Time dilation occurs near black holes - time passes slower the closer you get to the event horizon.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="info-card">
                    <div class="icon">‚≠ê</div>
                    <h3>Stars & Nebulae</h3>
                    <p>Our universe contains an estimated <span class="highlight">200 billion to 2 trillion galaxies</span>.</p>
                    <p>Proxima Centauri: Nearest star to Earth at <span class="highlight">4.24 light-years</span> away.</p>
                    <p>Orion Nebula: A stellar nursery containing <span class="highlight">thousands of young stars</span> forming from cosmic dust.</p>
                    <p>Sirius: Brightest star visible from Earth, <span class="highlight">8.6 light-years</span> away.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="info-card">
                    <div class="icon">üåç</div>
                    <h3>Earth & Moon</h3>
                    <p>Earth's age: <span class="highlight">4.54 billion years</span>.</p>
                    <p>Distance from Earth to Moon: <span class="highlight">384,400 kilometers</span>.</p>
                    <p>Moon's diameter: <span class="highlight">3,474 kilometers</span> (27% of Earth's diameter).</p>
                    <p>Moon takes <span class="highlight">27.3 days</span> to orbit Earth and controls our tides.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="info-card">
                    <div class="icon">üöÄ</div>
                    <h3>Space Exploration</h3>
                    <p>Voyager 1: Launched in <span class="highlight">1977</span>, now <span class="highlight">24+ billion kilometers</span> from Earth.</p>
                    <p>International Space Station orbits Earth every <span class="highlight">90 minutes</span> at altitude of <span class="highlight">408 kilometers</span>.</p>
                    <p>Mars: Fourth planet, distance of <span class="highlight">225 million kilometers</span> at closest approach.</p>
                    <p>Humans last walked on the Moon in <span class="highlight">1972</span> during Apollo 17 mission.</p>
