        <div id="world" class="content-section">
            <h2 class="section-title">World Records & Wonders</h2>
            <div class="info-grid">
                <div class="info-card">
                    <div class="icon">üèîÔ∏è</div>
                    <h3>Mount Everest</h3>
                    <p>Height: <span class="highlight">8,849 meters</span> (29,032 feet) above sea level.</p>
                    <p>Located in the <span class="highlight">Himalayas</span> on the Nepal-Tibet border.</p>
                    <p>First successfully summited in <span class="highlight">1953</span> by Edmund Hillary and Tenzing Norgay.</p>
                    <p>Temperature at summit: <span class="highlight">-40¬∞C</span> with wind speeds up to <span class="highlight">200 km/h</span>.</p>
                    <p>Over <span class="highlight">4,000 people</span> have reached the summit since 1953.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="info-card">
                    <div class="icon">üè¢</div>
                    <h3>Burj Khalifa</h3>
                    <p>World's tallest building at <span class="highlight">828 meters</span> (2,717 feet).</p>
                    <p>Located in <span class="highlight">Dubai, United Arab Emirates</span>.</p>
                    <p>Completed in <span class="highlight">2010</span> and has <span class="highlight">163 floors</span> above ground.</p>
                    <p>Contains <span class="highlight">900 residential units</span> and luxury apartments.</p>
                    <p>Elevator reaches top in <span class="highlight">60 seconds</span>.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="info-card">
                    <div class="icon">üåä</div>
                    <h3>Mariana Trench</h3>
                    <p>Deepest point: <span class="highlight">10,994 meters</span> (36,070 feet) deep.</p>
                    <p>Located in the <span class="highlight">Western Pacific Ocean</span> near Guam.</p>
                    <p>Pressure at bottom: <span class="highlight">1,100 times atmospheric pressure</span>.</p>
                    <p>Only 3 crewed expeditions have reached the bottom.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="info-card">
                    <div class="icon">üèéÔ∏è</div>
                    <h3>Fastest Land Speed</h3>
                    <p>Record: <span class="highlight">1,227.986 km/h</span> (763.035 mph) set in <span class="highlight">2022</span>.</p>
                    <p>Set by Andy Green in the Bloodhound LSR vehicle.</p>
                    <p>Previous record held for <span class="highlight">40+ years</span> at 1,190 km/h.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="info-card">
                    <div class="icon">üèä</div>
                    <h3>Pacific Ocean</h3>
                    <p>Largest ocean: <span class="highlight">165.2 million km¬≤</span> in area.</p>
                    <p>Covers approximately <span class="highlight">46%</span> of world's ocean surface.</p>
                    <p>Average depth: <span class="highlight">4,280 meters</span>.</p>
                    <p>Contains more than <span class="highlight">46,000 islands</span>.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="info-card">
                    <div class="icon">üåâ</div>
                    <h3>Longest Bridge</h3>
                    <p>Danyang-Kunshan Grand Bridge: <span class="highlight">164.8 kilometers</span> long.</p>
                    <p>Located in <span class="highlight">China</span> on the Beijing-Shanghai High-Speed Railway.</p>
                    <p>Completed in <span class="highlight">2011</span> and cost approximately <span class="highlight">$8.5 billion</span>.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="info-card">
                    <div class="icon">üè†</div>
                    <h3>Great Pyramid of Giza</h3>
                    <p>Originally <span class="highlight">146.6 meters</span> tall (now 138.5m).</p>
                    <p>Base: <span class="highlight">230.4 meters</span> on each side.</p>
                    <p>Built in <span class="highlight">2560 BC</span> during Pharaoh Khufu's reign.</p>
                    <p>Contains approximately <span class="highlight">2.3 million stone blocks</span>, each weighing 2-80 tons.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="info-card">
                    <div class="icon">üèÉ</div>
                    <h3>Fastest Human Speed</h3>
                    <p>100-meter sprint record: <span class="highlight">9.58 seconds</span> by Usain Bolt.</p>
                    <p>Average speed during sprint: <span class="highlight">37.57 km/h</span>.</p>
                    <p>Peak speed reached: <span class="highlight">44.72 km/h</span> between 60-80 meters.</p>
